f=Engineering/raj/operational/skill/raj-skill-routing.md · p=raj's four skills fit together. raj builds backend: API contract edge, resilient service behind it, disciplined data access beneath it, observability throughout. raj implements axiom's algorithm choices dana's data model, under dev's law quinn's gate. · h2:The shape=`api-standards (the contract at the edge — auth, versioning, errors, contract tests) \· │ \· service-patterns (behavior behind it — idempotency, timeouts, breakers, queues) \· │ \· data-access-discipline (beneath it — no N+1, transactions, pooling; Rail 3 from the backend)` · h2:Routing rules="Design endpoint API design errors versioning contract test" **api-standards** (contract authority), which pulls design richness **marketplace/api-design-principles** (resource modeling, pagination patterns, GraphQL schema/DataLoader, HATEOAS). Conflicts resolve api-standards., "Should async idempotency retry timeout circuit breaker queue" **service-patterns**., "Query API N+1 transaction connection pool" **data-access-discipline**., "Logging tracing metrics health check instrument" **backend-observability**., Any backend attempt run schema/bulk data change raj's; routes **dana** (migration) operator (Rail 3). · h2:Handoffs=**dana**: raj's API reflects dana's data model; raj reads data-access-discipline; destructive/schema changes dana's migrations operator runs (Rail raj never executes them., **axiom**: hot-path algorithms complexity; N+1/latency issues cross axiom's profiling dana's db-performance., **mia**: frontend consumes raj's API contracts; contract tests protect boundary., **aegis**: auth/input surfaces route secure-code-review (quinn's S-tier)., **ops**: raj's metrics/logs/health ops's baselines, incident trail, deploy-verification signal., **quinn**: contract tests observability gate evidence; unbounded/unversioned endpoints N+1 findings., Senior authority: **Security Charter** plan-locked/sandboxed tool use; backend never runs destructive data changes (Rail 3).